HEADWORD: Stupeous
<hw>Stu"pe*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stupa</ets>, or better <ets>stuppa</ets>, tow; cf. L.
<ets>stuppeus</ets> made of tow. Cf. <er>Stupose</er>.]</ety>
<def>Resembling tow; having long, loose scales, or matted filaments,
like tow; stupose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stupid</ent>⟦br⟧
